              TRIM28
              , which encodes a scaffold protein involved in DNA repair and genome stability. They then screened a cohort of 269 cases and found 8 more patients bearing
              TRIM28
              loss‐of‐function mutations. The gene appears to function as a tumor suppressor with loss of heterozygosity in the tumor cells.},
